        "text_JNrCVJ": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p><strong>Rombe's Rooftop Revolution: Cedar Hospitality's Culinary Partnership</strong></p><p>Step into Rombe, Burwood East’s newest rooftop gem, where an urban farm meets culinary excellence! Nestled atop a shopping centre, this 2500-square-metre marvel at Burwood Brickworks is more than just a place to dine – it's an experience.</p><p><strong>Key Highlights:</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Breathtaking Ambiance:</strong> Enjoy a light-filled dining area with a barn-style A-frame and floor-to-ceiling windows that offer stunning garden views.</li><li><strong>Flexible Space:</strong> Perfect for any occasion with seating for 120 and standing room for up to 350 in The Glass House for larger events.</li><li><strong>Seasonal Delights:</strong> Head Chef Jerry Yi, with his rich culinary background (ex Shihuishi and Red Spice Road), curates an all-day menu showcasing the best local, seasonal produce.</li><li><strong>Impressive Drinks List:</strong> Savor expertly crafted cocktails that elevate your dining experience.</li></ul><p><strong>Why Rombe is Special:</strong> From breakfast and lunch to soon-to-be-launched dinner services starting late April, Rombe promises a seamless transition from day to night. This venue captures Melbourne’s essence with its focus on fresh, local ingredients and modern Australian cooking techniques.</p><p>We at Cedar Hospitality are thrilled to support Rombe’s journey! Our Account Manager, Jerry, has transformed their kitchen with top-notch Electrolux ovens and a bespoke Scheer Proline Charcoal Rotisserie & Grill. Witness the magic that comes from a well-fitted kitchen and passionate chefs!</p><p>📍 <strong>Visit Rombe:</strong> Experience the magic at Burwood Brickworks, Burwood East.</p>",
